Assignment name  : str_maxlenoc 
Expected files   : str_maxlenoc.c
Allowed functions: write, malloc, free
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a program that takes one or more lines and displays, followed by a line break, the longest line that appears in each parameter.
If multiple strings match, the one that appears first in the first parameter will be displayed. Note that a blank line can technically appear on any line.
If there are no parameters, the program will display a new string ('\n').

Example:

$>./str_maxlenoc ab bac abacabccabcb
a
$>./str_maxlenoc bonjour salut bonjour bonjour
u
$>./str_maxlenoc xoxAoxo xoxAox  oxAox oxo  A ooxAoxx oxooxo Axo | cat -e
$
$>./str_maxlenoc bosdsdfnjodur atehhellosd afkuonjosurafg headfgllosf fghellosag afdfbosnjourafg
os
$>./str_maxlenoc | cat -e
$